  "texts": [
    "While all models say yes, we evaluate for the following keywords that are specific for Exudyn, namely multibody, simulation, rigid and flexible bodies, connectors, Python and C++.",
    "If most of these keywords are present in the answer, we consider the LLM to know the library, meaning that the according GitHub files have been used for training.",
    "The results of these tests are summarized in Table 5 and the responses are given in Appendix A.2.",
    "It is clearly shown that only GPT-3.5, GPT-4, and Bard have been trained with sources and documentation of Exudyn, while LLaMA-2 cannot generate information clearly related to Exudyn, in particular containing a wrong focus on powder dynamics.",
    "Example 3: Create a mass-spring-damper in ExudynThis example is aiming to create the simulation model of a linear mass-spring-damper undergoing a constant force with Exudyn."
